The first one does spawn level with your current position, but then the next one will spawn at a lower height then you. The third one will be level with you again, and the fourth one will spawn higher up. Then the pattern repeats.

Alright, this later-world level contains a new type of enemy-- ghost bats. As you can see right here, you cannot harm them with your shots. So, you have no choice but to avoid them.

So, yeah. As I did there, bait a "level with you" ghost to spawn above the hallway, then quickly dash down the hallway, grab the gem, then get outta there before the next "level with you" ghost can get you.
Alright, let me try to get some mana back and then I'll continue upward.

Oh, man. Be careful of the bouncing gummy blocks here. You could easily fly out of control. However, one nice thing is that whenever you touch a bouncing gummy block, you recover a little bit of mana.

So, yeah. Touch a bouncing gummy block, and you get bounced away from it. Now, the next new thing here is this new enemy, the shooter. He just sits there, shooting periodically. Avoid his > shots and shoot him right back!
Okay, now the darker blocks here are a type of block that only enemies can pass through. You can't go through them yourself, so you must go around the whole hairpin turn here.
